default 
defaultextend its activities from radio and TV to onli
defaultne. This is reflected in the 2006
default 
defaultFramework Agreement as ʻa comprehensive online content service, with content
default 
defaultserving the whole range of the BBCʼs Public Purposesʼ, meaning that the extension
default 
defaultto online is to be a wholesale one.
default&#xa0;
defaultAs above shown the BBC has
default taken full advantage of this carte blanche and it has
default 
defaultspent highly - at an annual rate of £177m (2012/13 BBC Financial Statements) 
default–
default in
default 
defaultestablishing its commanding presence for news online, although as noted in the
default 
defaultstatistics section (pp. 15 &amp; 16) users o
defaultf news websites rated Sky as fully equivalent
default 
defaultto the BBC for accuracy &amp; reliability, trustworthiness and impartiality &amp; lack of bias.
default&#xa0;
defaultWhat then is so very serious and concerning about the BBCʼs so establishing itself in
default 
defaultthe new communications medium of on
defaultline? An indication was given very recently by
default 
defaultthe Home Secretary in a speech she gave to a gathering of the Society of Editors. In
default 
defaulther speech Mrs May made the following observations.
default&#xa0;
default“
defaultLocal newspapers are having a particularly hard time. That has been pa
defaultrtly the
default 
